l not answer: yea, twice; but I will proceed no further.","year":-1520},{"id":"recJXZqjeFSFU0zAw","ref":"Job.40.6","text":"Then answered the LORD unto Job out of the whirlwind, and said,","year":-1520},{"id":"recxLCcSvvLDhghdP","ref":"Job.40.7","text":"Gird up thy loins now like a man: I will demand of thee, and declare thou unto me.","year":-1520},{"id":"rec40AUa3cs6Did6k","ref":"Job.40.8","text":"Wilt thou also disannul my judgment? wilt thou condemn me, that thou mayest be righteous?","year":-1520}]}
